<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="415" pageId="25" pageNumber="414" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[242,1474,1687,1850]" pageId="25" pageNumber="414">DESCRIPTION. — Shell pyriform, light, opaque. Protoconch paucispiral, wide, dome-shaped, smooth. Spire short, teat-like, one whorl. Aperture narrow, oblique. Base tapering. Outer lip thick, slightly more reflected over its middle part, shoulder rounded, outer edge arched over its posterior part, rather straight over its anterior part, outer margin thickened, wide, stepped. Inner edge bearing about 14 very weak, quite indistinct, labial denticles. Four columellar plaits, first subvertical, very angled at its posterior part, 3 uppermost plaits horizontal, decreasing in size.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1443,266,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Ground colour whitish, spire pale orange, 2 wide spiral bands on the last whorl, encompassing the whole outer margin, base of the columella and siphonal canal intense white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1443,266,394]" box="[242,559,335,359]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">
Dimensions: 6.63 x 
<quantity box="[456,555,335,359]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.70 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1443,266,394]" box="[242,433,370,394]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Radula unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="415" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1444,439,672]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">
REMARKS. — In its suboval outline and its narrow aperture, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boyer" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Cossignani" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[856,1007,440,464]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatrix">
<emphasis box="[856,1007,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrata beatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles the French Polynesian 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redfield" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[212,383,474,498]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="translata">
<emphasis box="[212,383,474,498]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrata translata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 4). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boyer" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Cossignani" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[486,639,474,498]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatrix">
<emphasis box="[486,639,474,498]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrata beatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redfield" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[782,899,474,498]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="translata">
<emphasis box="[782,899,474,498]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">S. translata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its more pyriform outline, its more protruding spire, its slightly less narrow aperture, its more flexuous outer lip, its angled first columellar plait and its horizontal 3 uppermost plaits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[212,1444,439,672]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">
The species was described originally in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coovert &amp; Coovert" authorityYear="1995" box="[769,909,579,602]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrataginella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[769,909,579,602]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrataginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, here considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jousseaume" authorityYear="1875" box="[1316,1389,578,601]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1316,1389,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, the shell morphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boyer" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Cossignani" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[591,688,613,637]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="beatrix">
<emphasis box="[591,688,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">S. beatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be closer to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redfield" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[929,1045,613,637]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="translata">
<emphasis box="[929,1045,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">S. translata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to the East African “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1434,614,637]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Marginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1434,614,637]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Marginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName authority="Clover, 1974" authorityName="Clover" authorityYear="1974" box="[212,403,647,671]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrataginella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spryi">
<emphasis box="[212,262,648,671]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">spryi</emphasis>
Clover, 1974
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus box="[413,459,648,672]" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Coovert &amp; Coovert" authorityYear="1995" box="[575,715,649,672]" class="Gastropoda" family="Marginellidae" genus="Serrataginella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="26" pageNumber="415" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,715,649,672]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="415">Serrataginella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
